# {{PROJECT_NAME}} - working rules

Guidance for Cursor (and any agent) working in this repo. Keep it short; the detail lives in
[`docs/`](../../docs/). Start there before non-trivial work. The same guidance drives
[`CLAUDE.md`](../../CLAUDE.md) and [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).

## Always

- **Commit after every small fix or task.** One logical change per commit,
  [Conventional Commits](../../CONTRIBUTING.md), imperative summary. Small commits beat big ones.
{{#TWO_BRANCH}}
- **Two long-lived branches.** Feature work integrates on `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`; `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
  is promoted to the always-deployable `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` via a periodic release PR. Never merge
  a feature branch straight into `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`.
- **One directory per branch (worktrees).** Never commit directly to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` or
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. Create each task's branch as its own worktree with
  `{{WT_CMD}} new <type>/<slug>` (e.g. `{{WT_CMD}} new fix/scroll-jitter`), which branches off
  `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`, and do all work inside the printed worktree path. Clean up merged worktrees
  with `{{WT_CMD}} gc`.
- **Follow the task lifecycle.** "Do task X from the backlog" means: fetch, create the worktree
  (off `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`), work in small commits, run the quality gate, push, open a PR into
  `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` (referencing the task), then hand it off for review. Never self-merge.
{{/TWO_BRANCH}}
{{#SINGLE_BRANCH}}
- **One long-lived branch (trunk).** Feature work integrates directly on the always-deployable
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. There is no separate integration branch and no release PR; a feature branch
  merges into `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` once it is green.
- **One directory per branch (worktrees).** Never commit directly to `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`. Create
  each task's branch as its own worktree with `{{WT_CMD}} new <type>/<slug>`
  (e.g. `{{WT_CMD}} new fix/scroll-jitter`), which branches off `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`, and do all
  work inside the printed worktree path. Clean up merged worktrees with `{{WT_CMD}} gc`.
- **Follow the task lifecycle.** "Do task X from the backlog" means: fetch, create the worktree
  (off `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}`), work in small commits, run the quality gate, push, open a PR into
  `{{MAIN_BRANCH}}` (referencing the task), then hand it off for review. Never self-merge.
{{/SINGLE_BRANCH}}
- **Fetch before starting work.** `git fetch` at the start of a session and before creating a
  new branch.
- **English** in code, comments, docs, commits. {{COPY_LANGUAGE_NOTE}}
- **No emojis, no fancy dashes** anywhere. Regular hyphen `-` only.
- **Docs + `CHANGELOG.md` change in the same PR** as the code they describe.

